{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data structure that represents a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"condition. Threads can block on a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" if they find a certain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"condition to be false. If other threads change the state of this","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"condition they signal the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", and that causes the waiting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threads to be woken up.","type":"text"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Cond","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider the following example of a shared variable.  One or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads can wait for data to be published to the variable and when"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"another thread publishes the data, it can signal one of the waiting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threads to wake up to collect the data.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is an example for using GCond to block a thread until a condition"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is satisfied:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"code":["  gpointer current_data = NULL;","  GMutex data_mutex;","  GCond data_cond;","","  void","  push_data (gpointer data)","  {","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    current_data = data;","    g_cond_signal (&data_cond);","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","  }","","  gpointer","  pop_data (void)","  {","    gpointer data;","","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    while (!current_data)","      g_cond_wait (&data_cond, &data_mutex);","    data = current_data;","    current_data = NULL;","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","","    return data;","  }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Whenever a thread calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"pop_data()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" now, it will wait until","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"current_data is non-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", i.e. until some other thread","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"has called ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"push_data()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The example shows that use of a condition variable must always be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"paired with a mutex.  Without the use of a mutex, there would be a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"race between the check of "},{"code":"current_data","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" by the while loop in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"pop_data()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and waiting. Specifically, another thread could set","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"current_data"},{"type":"text","text":" after the check, and signal the cond (with nobody"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"waiting on it) before the first thread goes to sleep. ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"specifically useful for its ability to release the mutex and go"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to sleep atomically."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also important to use the "},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"g_cond_wait_until()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions only inside a loop which checks for the condition to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"true.  See ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for an explanation of why the condition may","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not be true even after it returns."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is allocated in static storage then it can be used"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"without initialisation.  Otherwise, you should call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"on it and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_clear()"},{"type":"text","text":" when done."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" should only be accessed via the g_cond_ functions."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an